Hello fellow crawlers,

At Luxembourg&#39;s national library we&#39;re taking our first steps in crawling. I&#39;m looking at this myself at the moment, I&#39;ve managed to successfully crawl, store, search, retrieve and display some sites as a prototype, using H1.2 for the crawling part. When I installed H1.4 a month ago, it didn&#39;t work and I assumed an interference issue with 1.2 (an environment variable or something), but after a new clean server installation (re-installing SuSe Enterprise 9 and then H1.4) I get the same error as soon as I try the first default job (using one seed, having set the &quot;user-agent&quot; and &quot;from&quot; fields correctly):

Symptoms: 

- The job completes almost as soon as it starts, 
- &quot;No statistics associated with job&quot; in the reports
- No page is crawled or archived (specified arcs folder isn&#39;t even created)
- on the Jobs tab under &quot;Completed jobs&quot; I read &quot;Could not launch job - Fatal initializationException - A fatal InitializationException occured when loading job:Unable to setup crawl modules: java.lang.NullPointerException: Reference Queue cannot be null&quot;. 

What am I missing? Does any part of the job initialzation differ signigicantly from H1.2? 

Any ideas or hints greatly appreciated.

Charlie

--Boundary_(ID_fM4tuaPf69Z6XE/EIxMBZg)
